The chamber holding the &quot;lightbulb&quot; tubes can indeed be reinforced, but the end must be open, and the glass tube must be in an open space.<br>
<br>
The danger with any shutdown or sealing system - active or passive - is the potential for it to activate at the wrong time , thus CAUSING the failure. This is VERY common in engineered systems.<br>
